rComments: hes very passionate about the material and it shows! in terms of test, you're very limited on the time given so make sure you know your stuff before going into it. SA from lectures, definitions from text and lecture, and MCQ is from text (so its section is a bit harder. he does repeat some SA from past exams. overall i learnt a lot and enjoyed!
He is an amazing professor. Uses past questions on his exam. Took 2-3 courses with him, and never been disappointed.

It's not hard to get a C+ or B (UofT avg) but to get an A you really need to do some work.. Great Prof, love his lectures, they way he delivers the content is very interesting and makes you want to listen/know more. Enjoyed the class very much even though we had 9AM class.

Prof Kamenetsky sets out clear expectations, he tests you on what he teaches you. The lectures are interesting . He is extremely approachable and does his best to help. Tests are tough, take VERY detailed textbook notes for MC. SA is directly from lectures, but you need to attend the lectures and take good notes in order to do well.

Lectures were very interesting, he seemed to be quite passionate to talk about the topic  or maybe he really enjoys teaching in general?  Gave very detailed instructions on the essay, which was extremely helpful. Tests and exam: avg difficulty,  past tests are useful but dont rely on it 100%.

He's a good professor. He listens to his students but sometimes just watching people walk up to him and ask questions during the break, its as if he gets bored listening to students talk... which is weird. The material he teaches is extremely interesting but it is tested very specifically (need past tests).

Repeats short answers from past two years worth of tests, no new questions. changes m.c and defintions. fairly easy if you attend lectures and take DETAILED notes. Got an A+ , explains well but doesn't really matter because you just have to memorize it for the test. He's realy nice and helpful

His lectures are clear and easy to follow. You must attend lectures. Repeats past tests. However, he is very rude and condescending when you ask him a question he deems 'stupid.' Not that he's said a question is stupid, just the way he replies is enough to discourage you for a couple weeks. Teaches well but I'd never take his class again
He is a really good prof. You have to attend all of his classes. Tests/exams are based mainly on lecture material and past tests with minor changes.

He is the best. When it comes to student concerns he is always there to help. He replies to emails fast and he is always available to meet students who need it. He really does care!! He also seems to genuinely want the best for his students. I felt he wanted me to succeed- Rarely do I feel that from anyone. He is a great prof & person.

Having taken all three of his courses, I feel that he is among the best profs at UTM.  He genuinely cares about his students and always takes the time to listen and answer concerns.  Lectures are always interesting, especially in 442 where he incorporates field trips and guest speakers that bring textbook theory to life. Lucky to have had him.

I don't really care about social psychology. I found the material in this class very dry and unfortunately very hetero-normative, which was a shame. He is a nice person and good lecturer, though. I didn't read the textbook at all and still got an 85 in the class. Study from past tests and pick a good topic for the essay.

He repeated too much in lectures and talked too much about his children and family stories that I found pretty useless. I dont think he meant in but he came off as rude sometimes. tried his best to help but i hated his class
classes are interesting, he cares about the subject. test sa marked very difficultly, and probably the hardest mc's you will ever see.
Really great with explanations, and his tests are fairly reasonable if you study past tests and memorize the answers. He can be quite condescending at times though.
Excellent Professor!  Very kind and knows his topics extremely well.  Pleased to have met such a wonderful and caring professor at UTM.

I'd read the textbook before coming to class.  Also, sit at the front.  My experience-his voice makes me so sleepyyy.  It's so languid and monotone.  But I think he's quite good looking so that helped me stay awake.  That aside, he's super fair, knows his stuf, explains materials clearly, and treats everyone as his colleagues.  I like him, overall.

definitely monotonous. he is discouraging to students (as mentioned in another rating). he suggested that i find another field of study. was not encouraging nor did he offer any other type of advice as to why he said that. disappointed that he's the head of psych dept
TEACHES COURSES AT UNIVERSITY AT THE LEVEL THEY SHOULD BE TAUGHT! STRUCTURES IT WELL SO YOU PROGRESS FAST! GREAT PROF! BIT BORING SOMETIMES
AMAZING-EXACTLY HOW PROFS SHOULD BE AND HOW CLASSES AT UNIVERSITY SHOULD BE TAUGHT!! HE'S SO HELPFUL AND HE IS ALWAYS AVAILABLE TO HELP HIS STUDENTS!
Great Prof
i recommend taking all his courses.

You definitely need to work extremely hard to earn an A in his course. The tests are easy if you know the textbook and his lectures inside out. The textbook part of his test requires you to know and write down the fine details that you think would be irrelevant, yet they show up on the test.

His expectations are incredibly reasonable. He expects you to work for your mark but he does reward good work. His lectures are fairly interesting. However, he is an incredibly cruel man who does not believe in sugar-coating. Take his courses but avoid his one-on-ones at all costs.

To get a good grade, he makes his students work really hard. However, if you do the work, your mark is totally in your control. That's very nice. He has always been very helpful and he is very hard working himself so no wonder that he expects a lot from students.

I think he is an awesome professor.  Those that do not like him or did not do well in his class probably did not attend lectures.  His tests are hard, but at the same time they are very fair.  He is one of the few professors that keeps his office doors open during his office hours.  He does want to help out students that put an effort.

As hard as it is, listen in class and take good notes and use them for your essay questions and you'll be fine. He's not the most interesting lecturer but a fair guy. Doesn't take a lot of interest in his students unless you're talking about his classes.
He is a nice guy but his class is tough.   Study for his exams!!!

EGADS! One of the most awful experiences at UofT was talking with Stuart. Imagine being in your final year and hearing that you'll never make it as a Psychologist. He told me to consider another field and it was not said it a nice way. Thank goodness I never had him as a teacher! Just a plain 'ol meanie!
BAD
Overrated. Monotonous 3 hour lectures coupled with a ridiculously complex textbook and equally difficult test questions. Stay away unless he changes the text.

Admittedly monotone...but go to his lectures and write down everything he says then put it all into your long answer questions (organized of course!). In this respect, very fair...all you gotta do is listen. MC questions are (often picky) details out of the text...read it carefully! Such a nice, nice man.
Makes you read a lot, more than should be required for a psych class.  Although the  information is interesting, he does expect a lot from his students.  Tests are also very hard
Expects a lot from his students
very good prof, explains everything in detail and as clear as possible.
always available for questions.
this guy is the cure for insomnia, but very helpful
hes an amazing teacher thanks to him im somewhere ive only dreamed of being his tests are fair and his lectures are tough but hes an amazing teacher
He is the most fair prof at U of T
Mr. Monotone..but a nice man.  His email replies are so damn brief though!

All the ratings below make sense. In my honest opinion, Dr. Kamenetsky is the ONLY good psychology prof at UTM. Very intelligent, kind, and gentle man. An asset to any program. Keep up the great work stuart!
best prof at UTM for sure...
Stuart is an excellent prof!!!
Very helpful prof
highly overrated prof...is alright tho...a stickler for details of text and lectures..memorize the lecture notes and all is well
very nice prof
Best prof I've ever had. I strongly recommend that you take his classes whenever you get the chance. Great prof, and a great guy. Fair and reasonable person.
No Comments
Easy prof but boring....LOL but its true!! He does look like Raymond from "Everybody Loves Raymond"
One of the best profs at U of T
Awesome prof and great guy. Really cares about your education. One of the best profs at UTM! TAKE EVERY COURSE HE TEACHES

If ur planning on taking this course, I would suggest taking it during the summer.  The prof himself said students do a lot better in the summer.  Kamenetsky is an excellent prof.  He explains concepts well and gives a lot of examples.  His tests r fair 2
Excellent prof !
Really Awesome prof
He does need sleep. His lectures are pretty boring sometimes. Makes me wanna go to sleep. He's super nice and friendly though. Too bad I'm not doing any more Psych courses.
I liked this Prof.  He was very thorough and Clear.  He also reminded me of Raymond, from evryboady loves Raymond.
Yes, he does tell everyone to do the specialist!! LoL. But his lectures are very concise and clear...wonderful class!
Gives good advice :) Even if he does tell everyone to take the specialist!
this dude needs some serious sleep ^_^
Voice reminds me of the doctor who created Frankenstein. He's a mad scientist.
very well organized in lectures, clear and understandable.  A true pleasure.
